    {
      "id": "jn-001",
      "url": "https://x.com/JeevanshuN/status/jn001",
      "created_at": "2026-04-28T22:51:00+05:30",
      "author": { "handle": "JeevanshuN", "name": "Jeevanshu Narang", "followers": 8800, "following": 540, "verified": false, "tier": "design" },
      "engagement": { "likes": 219, "reposts": 19, "replies": 17, "quotes": 5, "bookmarks": 52, "views": 16300 },
      "content": { "text": "Crazy times in design industry. Wanted to rant a bit about something I've been noticing.\n\nPeople with barely any real experience with AI are launching AI & design courses. You learnt what a PR and a merge is only a few weeks ago, calm down.\n\nSaw someone selling a PDF for 'how to crack interviews at top design companies'... for companies they couldn't crack themselves.\n\nFeels like when things get boring, people pivot to building an audience, and when that doesn't stick, they start selling courses.\n\nEveryone's chasing attention. Very few are building actual depth. And the cost? Early designers already anxious about AI end up paying for noise.\n\nIf you're an experienced designer who mentors aspiring designers, paid or free, I salute you.\n\nFor those early and liking the attention: please be responsible. There's a lot to learn.", "media_type": "text", "media_count": 0, "is_thread": false, "thread_len": 1, "has_link": false, "post_type": "original" },
      "_source": "real",
      "_followers_estimated": true
    },
